<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Lord
                                    <persName type="to">Pauncefote</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-09"><hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">Personal]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I beg to thank you for
                            your personal note of the 3d instant, and to inclose for your
                            information a copy of an instruction<note n="a" xml:id="d523fna">Printed
                                next below.</note> which I have sent to Mr. Choate, directing him to
                            formally request Lord Lansdowne to instruct His Majesty’s agent at Sofia
                            to take charge of United States interests in Bulgaria, as before.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>